an countries to bring them to a designated location for 14 days of medical observation.<ref>{{Cite web|title=\u8a18\u8005\u6703\u5feb\u8a0a\uff08\u63a5\u8f09\u5f9e\u6b50\u6d32\u795e\u6839\u5730\u5340\u8fd4\u9999\u6e2f\u7684\u672c\u6fb3\u6b50\u6d32\u7559\u5b78\u751f\u53ca\u5916\u904a\u6b50\u6d32\u7684\u6fb3\u9580\u5c45\u6c11\u5b89\u6392\uff09|url=https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/323219/|accessdate=2020-03-15|author=\u65b0\u805e\u5c40|date=2020-03-15|format=HTML|work=\u6fb3\u9580\u7279\u5225\u884c\u653f\u5340\u653f\u5e9c\u5165\u53e3\u7db2\u7ad9|publisher=|language=zh-hant|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315021412/https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/323219/|archivedate=2020-03-15|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, it was announced that starting 17 March at midnight (00:00), people arriving in Macau from any countries outside China (meaning mainland China, Hong Kong, Macau, and Taiwan) would have to undergo 14 days of medical observation at a designated location. The Tourism Bureau announced that transportation from Hong Kong International Airport to a designated location would be arranged for Macau residents and students coming from the United States as well as European countries.<ref name=\":37\">{{Cite web|title=\u660e\u65e5\u96f6\u6642\u8d77\u672c\u6fb3\u5c0d\u4e2d\u570b\u4ee5\u5916\u570b\u5bb6\u6216\u5730\u5340\u5165\u5883\u4eba\u58eb\u5be6\u65bd\u91ab\u5b78\u89c0\u5bdf\u63aa\u65bd \u547c\u7c72\u5165\u5883\u4eba\u58eb\u5165\u5883\u5982\u5be6\u7533\u5831 \u5c45\u6c11\u5982\u975e\u5fc5\u8981\u52ff\u5916\u904a|url=https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/323430/ |accessdate=2020-03-16 |author=\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72c0\u75c5\u6bd2\u611f\u67d3\u61c9\u8b8a\u5354\u8abf\u4e2d\u5fc3|date=2020-03-16 |format=HTML |work=\u6fb3\u9580\u7279\u5225\u884c\u653f\u5340\u653f\u5e9c\u5165\u53e3\u7db2\u7ad9 |publisher= |language=zh-hant |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316154242/https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/323430/ |archivedate=2020-03-16|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nEffective March 18, the government banned entry of all non-residents, with exceptions for mainland China, Hong Kong, and Taiwan.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://macaunews.mo/macau-prohibits-non-residents-from-entering-macau-with-the-exception-of-those-from-mainland-china-hong-kong-and-taiwan/|title=Macau Prohibits Non-Residents from Entering Macau with the exception of those from Mainland China, Hong Kong and Taiwan|website=Macau News |accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, the Tourism Bureau announced that from 19 March to 31 March, transportation from Hong Kong International Airport would take Macau residents and students coming from all countries to designated locations for medical observation.\n\nOn 19 March, the plan for resuming classes in stages was cancelled.<ref name=\":46\">{{Cite web|title=\u975e\u9ad8\u7b49\u6559\u80b2\u5b78\u6821\u5ef6\u671f\u5fa9\u8ab2\u81f3\u53e6\u884c\u518d\u516c\u5e03 |url=https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/323922/|accessdate=2020-03-19|author=\u6559\u80b2\u66a8\u9752\u5e74\u5c40|date=2020-03-19|format=|work=\u6fb3\u9580\u7279\u5225\u884c\u653f\u5340\u653f\u5e9c\u5165\u53e3\u7db2\u7ad9 |publisher=|language=zh-hant|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319114318/https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/323922/ |archivedate=2020-03-19|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, the chief executive announced that starting 25 March, connecting flights would no longer be permitted at [[Macau International Airport]]; any residents of Hong Kong, Taiwan, or mainland China who had been to other countries in the previous 14 days were prohibited from entering Macau; and Macau residents who had been to Hong Kong, Taiwan, or other countries in the past 14 days would be required to undergo 14 days of medical observation at a designated location.<ref name=\":56\">{{Cite web|title=\uff0d\u884c\u653f\u9577\u5b98\u8a18\u8005\u6703\u5feb\u8a0a\uff08\u660e\u8d77\u7981\u6b62\u5165\u5883\u524d14\u5929\u5167\u66fe\u5230\u5916\u570b\u7684\u975e\u6fb3\u9580\u5c45\u6c11\u5165\u5883\uff09\uff0d|url=https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/324556/|accessdate=2020-03-24|author=\u65b0\u805e\u5c40 |date=2020-03-24 |format=HTML |work=\u6fb3\u9580\u7279\u5225\u884c\u653f\u5340\u653f\u5e9c\u5165\u53e3\u7db2\u7ad9|publisher=|language=zh-hant|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200324031513/https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/324556/|archivedate=2020-03-24|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, the Health Bureau expanded restrictions on blood donations.<ref name=\":63\">{{Cite web|title=\u6350\u8840\u4e2d\u5fc3\u61c9\u5c0d\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72c0\u75c5\u6bd2\u80ba\u708e\u7684\u6700\u65b0\u63aa\u65bd\u548c\u547c\u7c72\u6350\u8840|url=https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/325006/|accessdate=2020-03-25|author=2020-03-25|date=2020-03-25|format=HTML|work=\u6fb3\u9580\u7279\u5225\u884c\u653f\u5340\u653f\u5e9c\u5165\u53e3\u7db2\u7ad9|publisher=|language=zh-hant|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325131008/https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/325006/|archivedate=2020-03-25|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===April 2020===\n\nOn 4 April, the government of Macau followed the Chinese central government in holding a day of mourning throughout Macau. [[Chinese flag]]s and [[Macau flag]]s were to be flown at [[half mast]], and public entertainment and celebrations or festive events were to stop. Starting at 10AM that day, Macau would observe a three-minute moment of silence.<ref>[https://hd.stheadline.com/news/realtime/hk/1739427/%E5%8D%B3%E6%99%82-%E6%B8%AF%E8%81%9E-%E7%96%AB%E6%83%85%E4%B8%8B%E5%85%A7%E5%9C%B0%E6%98%8E%E6%97%A5%E5%85%A8%E5%9C%8B%E5%93%80%E6%82%BC-%E6%BE%B3%E9%96%80%E5%B0%87%E4%B8%8B%E5%8D%8A%E6%97%97%E8%87%B4%E5%93%80 \u75ab\u60c5\u4e0b\u5167\u5730\u660e\u65e5\u5168\u570b\u54c0\u60bc \u6fb3\u9580\u5c07\u4e0b\u534a\u65d7\u81f4\u54c0]</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\n===Free medical treatment for patients from mainland China===\n\nAt a press conference, [[Ho Iat Seng]] welcomed mainland Chinese people to make use of Macau's free medical service. This created controversy online, with users worrying that people from the mainland would come to Macau and spread the virus. Afterwards, Secretary for Administration and Justice Zhang Yongchun (\u5f35\u6c38\u6625) said that any patients from outside Macau who had COVID-19 would need to pay their own medical bills; they would be able to apply for a fee waiver, and the government would make a decision based on their financial situation and effects on the public.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.macaodaily.com/html/2020-02/07/content_1414291.htm |title=\u885b\u5c40\uff1a\u4e0d\u7372\u6279\u8ffd\u6536\u9102\u5a66\u6cbb\u7642\u8cbb |date=2020-02-07 |work=\u6fb3\u9580\u65e5\u5831 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207134822/http://www.macaodaily.com/html/2020-02/07/content_1414291.htm |archivedate=2020-02-07 |url-status=live}}</ref> The first recovered patient<ref>{{Cite web|title=\u6fb3\u9580\u9996\u4f8b\u78ba\u8a3a\u75c5\u4eba\u4eca\u65e5\u5eb7\u5fa9\u51fa\u9662 \u7121\u65b0\u589e\u65b0\u578b\u51a0\u72c0\u75c5\u6bd2\u80ba\u708e\u78ba\u8a3a\u75c5\u4f8b|url=https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/317349/|accessdate=2020-03-03|author=\u885e\u751f\u5c40|date=2020-03-03|format=HTML|work=\u6fb3\u9580\u7279\u5225\u884c\u653f\u5340\u653f\u5e9c\u5165\u53e3\u7db2\u7ad9|publisher=|language=zh-hant|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303141814/https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/317349/|archivedate=2020-03-03|url-status=live}}</ref> was a businesswoman from Wuhan. The Health Bureau stated that medical fees for people from outside Macau were double the fees for locals. The patient had applied to waive 34,000 [[patacas]] in medical fees. Internet users investiaged and said that in the photos of her leaving the hospital, a handbag could be seen worth 20,000 patacas, and that the hotel she stayed at was more than 1000 patacas a night, concluding that she could afford the medical fees. This created a significant controversy. The bureau said they would make a determination in accordance with the law.<ref name=\":28\">{{Cite web |title=NEWS.GOV.MO: \u2014\u8a18\u8005\u6703\u5feb\u8a0a\uff08\u6709\u95dc\u73e0\u6d77\u65b0\u78ba\u8a3a\u75c5\u4f8b\u5728\u6fb3\u671f\u9593\u7684\u60c5\u6cc1\uff09\u2014 |url=https://news.gov.mo/detail/zh-hant/N20BGe1xc2 |accessdate=2020-02-07 |author=\u65b0\u805e\u5c40 |date=2020-02-07 |format=HTML |work=news.gov.mo |publisher=\u65b0\u805e\u5c40 |language=zh-hant |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207114546/https://news.gov.mo/detail/zh-hant/N20BGe1xc2?78 |archivedate=2020-02-07}}</ref>\n\nWhile in the hospital, the first confirmed patient requested [[hot dry noodles]], a dish from Wuhan, so the hospital specially arranged a Hubei chef. When leaving the hospital there were more expenses, causing locals to envy the patient's \"five-star service\". This caused controversy on the internet in both Macau and Hong Kong. The director of [[Conde S. Janu\u00e1rio Hospital]] Li Weicheng (\u674e\u5049\u6210) said that the hospital's goal is not to provide special meals to patients, but rather that nutrition is important for a patient's recovery; if the patient's nutrition is inadequate, it's bad for their recovery. He emphasized that all patients are treated equally with respect to meals, and that the cost of meals is included in the hospital bill.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://aamacau.com/2020/02/07/%E5%B1%B1%E9%A0%82%E3%80%8C%E6%98%9F%E7%B4%9A%E6%9C%8D%E5%8B%99%E3%80%8D%E6%83%B9%E5%B8%82%E6%B0%91%E7%9C%BC%E7%B4%85-%E6%9D%8E%E5%81%89%E6%88%90%EF%B8%B0%E4%BB%BB%E4%BD%95%E7%97%85%E4%BA%BA%E8%86%B3/ |title=\u5c71\u9802\u300c\u661f\u7d1a\u670d\u52d9\u300d\u60f9\u5e02\u6c11\u773c\u7d05 \u674e\u5049\u6210\ufe30\u4efb\u4f55\u75c5\u4eba\u81b3\u98df\u4e00\u8996\u540c\u4ec1 |date=2020-02-07 |work=aamacau |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207132930/https://aamacau.com/2020/02/07/%E5%B1%B1%E9%A0%82%E3%80%8C%E6%98%9F%E7%B4%9A%E6%9C%8D%E5%8B%99%E3%80%8D%E6%83%B9%E5%B8%82%E6%B0%91%E7%9C%BC%E7%B4%85-%E6%9D%8E%E5%81%89%E6%88%90%EF%B8%B0%E4%BB%BB%E4%BD%95%E7%97%85%E4%BA%BA%E8%86%B3/ |archivedate=2020-02-07|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Closing the border===\nWhen Guangdong became the province with the second-most cases in China, Macau still had tens of thousands of people going to and from Zhuhai every day. Many people asked for the border to be closed, but the government repeatedly said that a complete closure was not possible. Ho Iat Seng said, \"If we closed all the ports of entry, who would remove the trash? Who would handle security? How would we get fresh produce? These are the issues we're thinking about.\"<ref>{{Cite web |title=\u7576\u65b7\u4e0d\u65b7 \u53cd\u53d7\u5176\u4e82 \u9632\u63a7\u75ab\u6230 \u5c01\u95dc\u5236\u52dd |url=https://www.facebook.com/sonpou/posts/2487100484889511 |date=[2020-02-07] |work=\u8a0a\u5831 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200214044424/https://www.facebook.com/sonpou/posts/2487100484889511 |archivedate=2020-02-14 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=\u8cc0\u4e00\u8aa0\uff1a\u6fb3\u9580\u4e0d\u6703\u5c01\u95dc \u76ee\u524d\u7d93\u6fdf\u640d\u5931\u4ecd\u53ef\u627f\u64d4|url=http://www.aastocks.com/tc/stocks/news/aafn-con/NOW.990806/popular-news|accessdate=2020-02-14|author=|date=|format=|work=AASTOCKS.COM|publisher=|language=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200214044437/http://www.aastocks.com/tc/stocks/news/aafn-con/NOW.990806/popular-news|archivedate=2020-02-14|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Closing parks===\nIn February 2020, in order to prevent spread of the virus, the government announced that all country parks and municipal parks would be closed, to avoid crowds and reduce the risk of infection. Some residents were unhappy with this, feeling that the risk of transmission in the suburbs was very low, and that staying at home for a long time without going outside to exercise would increase the risk of other diseases.<ref>{{Cite web |title=\u3010\u4f86\u8ad6\u3011\u5e0c\u671b\u6297\u75ab\u671f\u9593\uff0c\u7559\u5e02\u6c11\u4e00\u7247\u90ca\u91ce |url=https://aamacau.com/2020/02/08/%E3%80%90%E4%BE%86%E8%AB%96%E3%80%91%E5%B8%8C%E6%9C%9B%E6%8A%97%E7%96%AB%E6%9C%9F%E9%96%93%EF%BC%8C%E7%95%99%E5%B8%82%E6%B0%91%E4%B8%80%E7%89%87%E9%83%8A%E9%87%8E/?fbclid=IwAR185INjm4R66IVO-BXByPA6SvnOBlRepdER4camVJj_a2UeyL4Ka9TqPak |accessdate=2020-02-08 |date=2020-02-08 |language=zh-Hant |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200208081302/https://aamacau.com/2020/02/08/%E3%80%90%E4%BE%86%E8%AB%96%E3%80%91%E5%B8%8C%E6%9C%9B%E6%8A%97%E7%96%AB%E6%9C%9F%E9%96%93%EF%BC%8C%E7%95%99%E5%B8%82%E6%B0%91%E4%B8%80%E7%89%87%E9%83%8A%E9%87%8E/?fbclid=IwAR185INjm4R66IVO-BXByPA6SvnOBlRepdER4camVJj_a2UeyL4Ka9TqPak |archivedate=2020-02-08 |url-status=live}}</ref> The Center for Disease Control and Prevention said that railings and similar could become a mode of transmission, that it's difficult to wear a mask when exercising, and that it's easy to end up starting a conversation if you run into a friend; these could all increase the risk of transmitting the virus. The government decided to close public recreation facilities in order to avoid community transmission.<ref>{{Cite web |title=NEWS.GOV.MO: \u2014\u8a18\u8005\u6703\u5feb\u8a0a\uff08\u95dc\u9589\u516c\u5171\u4f11\u61a9\u8a2d\u65bd\uff09\u2014 |url=https://news.gov.mo/detail/zh-hant/N20BHtzW6u |accessdate=2020-02-08 |author=\u65b0\u805e\u5c40 |date=2020-02-08 |format=HTML |publisher=\u6fb3\u9580\u7279\u5225\u884c\u653f\u5340\u653f\u5e9c\u65b0\u805e\u5c40 |language=zh-Hant |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200208114841/https://news.gov.mo/detail/zh-hant/N20BHtzW6u;jsessionid=AF76980FE619421B35986BA900394923.app02?0 |archivedate=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 February, the government announced that casinos would reopen starting 20 February, but at the same time warned that the epidemic remained serious and advised residents to stay home and avoid going out. In addition, public parks and other public facilities would remain closed. In response, some residents questioned whether these measures and recommendations were contradictory, saying sarcastically that the government doesn't let people go to the park to exercise but does let them them go to the casino to gamble.<ref>{{Cite web|title=\u9632\u75ab\u4e0d\u80fd\u300c\u864e\u982d\u86c7\u5c3e\u300d \u8607\u5609\u8c6a\uff1a\u7121\u6cd5\u63a5\u53d7\u653f\u5e9c\u300c\u534a\u5957\u679c\u65b7\u300d\uff5c\u8ad6\u76e1\u5a92\u9ad4 AAMacau|url=https://aamacau.com/2020/02/22/%e9%98%b2%e7%96%ab%e4%b8%8d%e8%83%bd%e3%80%8c%e8%99%8e%e9%a0%ad%e8%9b%87%e5%b0%be%e3%80%8d-%e8%98%87%e5%98%89%e8%b1%aa%ef%bc%9a%e7%84%a1%e6%b3%95%e6%8e%a5%e5%8f%97%e6%94%bf%e5%ba%9c%e3%80%8c%e5%8d%8a/|accessdate=2020-02-25|author=|date=2020-02-22|format=HTML|work=\u8ad6\u76e1\u5a92\u9ad4 AllAboutMacau Media|publisher=|language=zh-hant|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225090029/https://aamacau.com/2020/02/22/%e9%98%b2%e7%96%ab%e4%b8%8d%e8%83%bd%e3%80%8c%e8%99%8e%e9%a0%ad%e8%9b%87%e5%b0%be%e3%80%8d-%e8%98%87%e5%98%89%e8%b1%aa%ef%bc%9a%e7%84%a1%e6%b3%95%e6%8e%a5%e5%8f%97%e6%94%bf%e5%ba%9c%e3%80%8c%e5%8d%8a/|archivedate=2020-02-25|url-status=live}}</ref> The government responded that after an evaluation, the decision to reopen casinos was made to balance the needs of epidemic prevention and local workers' employment. When the casinos reopened, epidemic prevention measures would be required to protect the health of employees and guests.<ref>{{Cite web|title=\u5a1b\u6a02\u5834\u91cd\u958b\uff1a\u91cd\u8996\u98a8\u96aa\u3001\u7a69\u5b9a\u5c31\u696d|url=https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/319285/|accessdate=2020-02-25|author=\u535a\u5f69\u76e3\u5bdf\u5354\u8abf\u5c40|date=2020-02-18|coauthors=|format=HTML|publisher=|language=zh-hant|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225090726/https://www.gov.mo/zh-hant/news/319285/|archivedate=2020-02-25|url-status=live}}</ref> In addition, the government announced on 19 February that some parks would reopen.<ref name=\":21\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by dependent territory|Macau]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in China by city|Macau]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Macau]]\n[[Category:2020 in Macau]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Asia|Macau]]\n", "name_user": "John B123", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eClosing the border:Fixed date format error", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Macau"}
{"title_page": "Jimmy Ellis (boxer)", "text_new": "{{short description|American boxer}}\n{{Infobox boxer\n| name = Jimmy Ellis\n| image = Jimmy Ellis 1968.JPG\n| caption = Ellis in 1968\n| nickname = \n| realname = James Albert Ellis\n| weight = [[Heavyweight]]\n| height = 6 ft 1 in\n| reach = 76 in\n| nationality = American\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1940|2|24}}\n| birth_place = [[Louisville, Kentucky]], U.S.\n| death_date = {{death date and age|2014|5|6|1940|2|24}}\n| death_place = Louisville, Kentucky, U.S.\n| style = [[Orthodox stance|Orthodox]]\n| total = 53\n| wins = 40\n| KO = 24\n| losses = 12\n| draws = 1\n}}\n\n'''James Albert \"Jimmy\" Ellis''' (February 24, 1940 \u2013 May 6, 2014) was a mid-20th century American [[professional boxer]]. He won the vacant [[World Boxing Association|WBA]] [[heavyweight]] title in 1968 by defeating [[Jerry Quarry]], making one successful title defense in the same year against [[Floyd Patterson]], before losing to [[Joe Frazier]] in 1970.\n\n==Early life==\nHe was born one of ten children. His father, Walter, was a pastor, and Ellis was brought up as a Christian.<ref>Courier Journal</ref> As a teenager he worked in a cement finishing factory.<ref>New York Times</ref> He also sang in the local church choir, later joined by his wife Mary. He continued church involvement all his adult life. In his youth he admired the boxer [[Joe Louis]].<ref>New York Times, 6 May 2014</ref>\n\n==Amateur career==\nEllis got into boxing as a teenager after watching a friend box fellow [[Louisville, Kentucky|Louisville]] youngster [[Muhammad Ali]] (then known as Cassius Clay) on a local amateur boxing television show called [[Tomorrow's Champions]]. \"I had a friend of mine named Donnie Hall, and he fought Ali,\" Ellis said. \"Donnie lost, and I thought I could maybe be a fighter then.\" Ellis went with Hall to Louisville's Columbia Gym, where the coach was a police officer named [[Joe Elsby Martin, Sr.|Joe Martin]].<ref>[http://www.thomloverro.com/2004.htm The ''Washington Times'' \u2013 July 31, 2004]</ref>\n\nEllis won 59 of 66 amateur bouts and was a [[Golden Gloves]] champion. He boxed Ali twice as an amateur, with Ali winning the first bout and Ellis winning the second.\n\n==Professional career==\nEllis turned professional as a [[middleweight]] in 1961. Early in his pro career, he was trained and managed by [[Bud Bruner]]. With Bruner, he compiled a record of 15\u20135 (6 KOs). His five losses were decisions to top Middleweight contenders Holly Mims (whom he defeated in a rematch), Henry Hank, [[Rubin Carter|Rubin \"Hurricane\" Carter]], [[Don Fullmer]], and [[George Benton]]. This start probably helped his speed of punch, movement and finesse.\n\nAt the end of 1964, after losing three out of four fights, Ellis decided to leave Bruner. He later recalled Bruner fondly. \"I liked him, and I fought a lot of top-rated fighters when I was with him, but eventually I had to move on,\" Ellis said. \"He did me justice, and we always remained friends.\"<ref>The ''Courier-Journal'' \u2013 February 23, 1996</ref>\n\nEllis wrote a letter to an at first skeptical<ref>New York Times 6 may 2014</ref> [[Angelo Dundee]], the trainer of Ali, and asked him to handle his career. Dundee agreed to be both manager and trainer. Ellis became a sparring partner for Ali and fought on several of Ali's early pre-world championship undercards. Six of his first eight fights with Dundee were on an Ali undercards.<ref>[http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1080682/1/index.htm ''Sports Illustrated'' \u2013 December 11, 1967]</ref>\n\nBy the mid 1960s Ellis was fighting heavyweights. Being a tall natural athletic build he'd had increasing trouble keeping down to middleweight. [[Dr. Ferdie Pacheco]], who worked with both Ali & Ellis throughout their careers, called Ellis's development from middleweight to heavyweight one of the most dramatic he could recall.<ref>Ferdie's book ''Fight Doctor''</ref>\n\n===WBA heavyweight title eliminator matches===\nBy 1966, Ellis was fighting as a heavyweight. When Ali was stripped of the world title for refusing to enter the military, the [[World Boxing Association]] staged an eight-man tournament that featured most of the top heavyweight contenders. Ellis, who was ranked eighth in the world after eight consecutive wins, was invited to be in the tournament. [[Joe Frazier]], ranked second by the WBA, chose not to participate in the tournament. Instead, Frazier fought for the vacant [[New York State Athletic Commission]] World Heavyweight Championship, which he won with an eleventh-round knockout of [[Buster Mathis]].\n\nIn the opening round of the tournament, Ellis fought [[Leotis Martin]] on August 5, 1967 in [[Houston, Texas]]. Ellis, the betting underdog, battered Martin's face into a bloody mask, and the referee stopped the fight in the ninth round.\n\nEllis met [[Oscar Bonavena]] in the second round of the tournament. The fight took place on December 2, 1967 in [[Louisville, Kentucky]]. Ellis, once again the underdog, dropped Bonavena with a right once in the third round and once in the tenth. After twelve rounds, Ellis was awarded a unanimous decision. This fight was regarded as one of the best of his career. He seemed to be in control for most of the fight apart from the ninth round. Ellis advanced to the tournament final.<ref>Boxing history by Sam Andre, Hamlyn publisher. Fight films</ref>\n\n===WBA heavyweight champion===\nIn the tournament final, Ellis faced [[Jerry Quarry]], a slight betting favorite, on April 27, 1968 in [[Oakland, California]].<ref>Boxing history by Sam Andre, Hamlyn, & also fight videos</ref> In a dull fight, Ellis fought what ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'' called \"a tactical masterpiece\". A cautious Ellis won a 15-round split decision<ref>Sam Andre's Pictorial History of Boxing</ref> to capture the vacant WBA Heavyweight Championship. Quarry said, \"If they'd given me the decision, I'd have given it back. I didn't deserve it.\"<ref>[http://www.eastsideboxing.com/news.php?p=11773&more=1 \"Forty Years Ago: WBA Launches Heavyweight Tourney\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090615111854/http://www.eastsideboxing.com/news.php?p=11773&more=1 |date=2009-06-15 }}</ref><ref>[http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1081131/index.htm ''Sports Illustrated'' \u2013 May 6, 1968]</ref>\n\n===Title reign===\nIn his only successful title defense, Ellis defeated [[Floyd Patterson]] by a controversial 15-round decision on September 14, 1968 in [[Stockholm]], Sweden. Ellis, who suffered a broken nose in the second round, was awarded the decision by the referee, the sole judge. Many in the crowd of 30,000 disagreed with the decision and started chanting, \"Floyd champ!\" The ''[[New York Times]]'' scored the fight seven rounds to six for Ellis, with two even.<ref>The ''New York Times'' \u2013 September 15, 1968</ref>\n\nFollowing the defeat of Patterson, Ellis was out of the ring for seventeen months. He was going to fight [[Henry Cooper]] in the United Kingdom, even though the [[British Boxing Board of Control]] refused to recognize the fight as a world title bout: the BBBofC was affiliated with the [[World Boxing Council]], who stated that they would only recognize a fight between Joe Frazier and a suitable contender as being for the world title. The fight was postponed a couple of times and eventually cancelled because Cooper injured his knee.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=abYlAAAAIBAJ&sjid=8_QFAAAAIBAJ&pg=2347,5330686&dq=jimmy+ellis+henry+cooper+recognize&hl=en ''Washington Afro-American'' \u2013 September 30, 1969]</ref>  Ellis then planned to fight Bob Cleroux in [[Montreal]], but Cleroux lost what was supposed to be a tune-up fight against the lightly regarded Billy Joiner. Finally, Ellis was going to fight [[Gregorio Peralta]] in [[Argentina]], but promoters canceled the fight 24 hours before it was to take place because of poor ticket sales.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=CnoyAAAAIBAJ&sjid=HrkFAAAAIBAJ&pg=890,4475902&dq=jimmy+ellis+cleroux+joiner&hl=en ''The Montreal Gazette'' \u2013 July 22, 1971]</ref><ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=sMYQAAAAIBAJ&sjid=z5ADAAAAIBAJ&pg=4233,4108700&dq=peralta+jimmy+ellis&hl=en ''The Age'' \u2013 December 23, 1969]</ref>\n\n===Unification title match with Joe Frazier===\n{{unreferenced section|date=May 2014}}\nOn February 16, 1970, Ellis fought Joe Frazier to unify the World Heavyweight Championship at [[Madison Square Garden]] in New York City. The undefeated Frazier, a heavy betting favorite, proved to be too strong and powerful. Ellis, who had never been floored as a heavyweight, was knocked down twice in the fourth round by a relentless Frazier, and Angelo Dundee stopped the fight before the start of the fifth round. <ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/jimmy-ellis-boxer-who-became-world-heavyweight-champion-and-close-friend-sparring-partner-and-ring-9356810.html ''The Independent'' \u2013 May 12, 2014]</ref> It was the first knockout loss for Ellis.\n\n===Ellis vs. Ali===\nAfter winning his next three fights, Ellis fought Muhammad Ali in the [[Houston Astrodome]] on July 26, 1971. Angelo Dundee chose to work with Ellis for the fight. He was Ali's trainer, but he was both manager and trainer for Ellis. Working with Ellis meant that he would get a bigger share of the purse. Ali accepted the arrangement and got Harry Wiley, who had worked with [[Henry Armstrong]] and [[Sugar Ray Robinson]], to be his trainer for the Ellis fight.<ref>[http://www.secondsout.com/features/main-features/muhammad-ali-vs-jimmy-ellis-the-inevitable-fight---40-years-on Muhammad Ali vs. Jimmy Ellis: The Inevitable Fight \u2013 40 Years On]</ref>\n\nEllis fought well over the first three rounds, but the fight turned after Ellis was hurt by a right hand in the fourth round. The right hand \"hurt me so bad I couldn't really fight my best after that,\" Ellis said. \"It ruined me.\" The referee stopped the fight in the twelfth round as Ellis remained on his feet. No knockdowns were recorded throughout the fight.<ref>[http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1085128/index.htm ''Sports Illustrated'' \u2013 August 2, 1971]</ref>\n\n===Diminishing skills===\n{{refimprove section|date=March 2015}}\nAfter the loss to Ali, Ellis won his next eight fights by knockout. But on June 18, 1973, he fought [[Earnie Shavers]], who was 44\u20132 (43 KOs), at Madison Square Garden. Ellis, ranked fourth by the WBA, stunned Shavers with a chopping right to the jaw and backed him into a corner. Shavers took numerous shots in the corner before clinching. After the referee separated the fighters, Shavers put Ellis down for the count with a powerful single right uppercut to the chin. The time was 2:39 in the first round.<ref>[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=TIgxAAAAIBAJ&sjid=xqEFAAAAIBAJ&pg=6581,1058082&dq=shavers+jimmy+ellis&hl=en The ''Montreal Gazette'' \u2013 June 19, 1973]</ref>\n\nEllis came back with a knockout win against [[club fighter]] Memphis Al Jones, but with his skills in decline, he went winless in his next five fights. He lost a split decision to [[Boone Kirkman]], fought a draw with Larry Middleton, dropped decisions to [[Ron Lyle]] and [[Joe Bugner]], and was stopped in nine rounds in a rematch with [[Joe Frazier]].\n\nThe rematch with [[Joe Frazier]] took place in [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]], on March 2, 1975. Ellis trained at the Golden Bowl Gym in Camberwell, Melbourne with martial arts 4th Dan Gerry Scaife. Ellis won the first three rounds, but Frazier then picked up the intensity and took control. With Ellis bloody and battered, Angelo Dundee signaled for referee [[Bob Foster (boxer)|Bob Foster]] to stop the fight in the ninth round.\n\n===Retirement===\nOn May 6, 1975, in what would be his last fight, Ellis knocked out club fighter [[Carl Baker (boxer)|Carl Baker]] in the first round. He retired aged 35 after suffering a training injury that left him partially blind in his left eye. Ellis finished with a record of 40\u201312\u20131 (24 KOs).\n\n==Later life==\nAfter retiring from boxing, Ellis trained boxers. Later he worked for the Louisville Parks Department on athletic and recreational projects between 1989 and 2003.<ref>''New York Times'', 6 May 2014</ref> In 2004, Ellis told the ''Washington Times'' \"...All I ever wanted to be was a good fighter and good man.'<ref>''New York Times'', 6 May 2014</ref> He seemed to achieve it. Brother Jeff gave a tribute on his death saying \" He was someone you could model yourself on\"<ref>Wiky sports, May 2014</ref> Ellis was a reserved family man who shunned flash although had a determined competitive streak in boxing.\n\nWith wife Mary he had six children,2 sons and 4 daughters. His brother Charles boxed in the 1964 Olympics.\nEllis was personally kind and gracious. He maintained a brotherly relationship with Ali over all the decades. Ali himself often recalled Ellis as a great friend. Ellis wasn't always pleased by the sparring partner tag but felt he had proved himself above that.<ref>''New York Times'' 6 May 2014</ref>\n\nHe suffered from [[dementia pugilistica]], for over a decade before his death.<ref>Bloomberg News, May 2014</ref> It was reported that Ellis' condition was so bad that he believed his deceased wife, Mary who died in 2006, was still alive.<ref>[http://www.braggingrightscorner.com/floresellis031709.html \"Jimmy Ellis: From Ali Sparring Partner To Heavyweight Champion\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708091127/http://www.braggingrightscorner.com/floresellis031709.html |date=2011-07-08 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.petemccormack.com/blog/?p=1522 \"The Sweet Science: Boxing And Getting One's Head Examined\"]</ref>\n\n==Death==\nEllis died at the age of 74 from complications of dementia on May 6, 2014, in Louisville Baptist Hospital, Kentucky.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-05-06/jimmy-ellis-ali-s-friend-who-won-heavyweight-crown-dies-at-74.html| publisher = Bloomberg | date = May 6, 2014 | accessdate = May 7, 2014 | title = Jimmy Ellis, Ali's Friend Who Won Heavyweight Crown, Dies at 74 | first = Stephen | last = Miller | first2= David | last2 = Henry}}</ref> On 12 May 2014 a funeral for his body was held at Louisville's Canaan Christian Church,<ref>TV News report of the Jimmy Ellis' funeral, WLKY News Louisville, published on Youtube 12 May 2014. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ltax6sZavyA</ref> which was afterwards buried in the city's Green Meadows Memorial Cemetery.<ref>Entry for Jimmy Ellis' grave in Findagrave website (2019). https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/129313194/jimmy-ellis</ref>\n\n==Tributes==\nOn the announcement Ellis' death [[Muhammad Ali]] issued the following statement: \"In the world of heavyweights I always thought him one of the best\".<ref>''New York Times'' 6 May 2014.</ref> \n\n==Personal life==\nEllis was survived by three brothers and a sister.<ref>''Courier Journal'', May 2014.</ref> His son Jeff played professional football and confirmed the family were always immensely proud of Ellis's achievements and his World Title.<ref>''Courier Journal'', May 2014.</ref> Ellis's family considered that boxing exacerbated the dementia of his later years, but had not necessarily caused it.<ref>'Courier Journal', May 2014.</ref> His younger brother Jeff, who'd trained with Ellis, commented that he himself now avoided watching boxing as he'd seen too many damaged by it.<ref>''New York Times'', 6 May 2014.</ref>\n\n==Professional boxing record==\n{{BoxingRecordSummary\n|draws=1\n|ko-wins=24\n|ko-losses=4\n|dec-wins=16\n|dec-losses=8\n}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%\"\n|-\n!{{abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Result\n!Record\n!Opponent\n!Type\n!Round, time\n!Date\n!Location\n!Notes\n|-\n|53\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|40\u201312\u20131\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|TTO}} Carl Baker\n